conditions.name: Cycle 1 Dosing Criteria - Bilirubin
conditions.description: Hepatic function requirement for weekly dosing in Cycle 1
conditions.text: Total bilirubin ≤1.5x upper limit of normal (ULN) or baseline (whichever is greater)

conditions.name: Cycle 1 Dosing Criteria - ALT/AST Low Baseline
conditions.description: Hepatic function requirement for weekly dosing in Cycle 1 when baseline is low
conditions.text: ALT and AST ≤3x ULN, if baseline <1.5x ULN

conditions.name: Cycle 1 Dosing Criteria - ALT/AST High Baseline
conditions.description: Hepatic function requirement for weekly dosing in Cycle 1 when baseline is elevated
conditions.text: ALT and AST ≤2x baseline, if baseline ≥1.5x ULN

conditions.name: New Cycle Dosing Criteria - AE Resolution
conditions.description: Adverse event resolution requirement for new cycle
conditions.text: Ramucirumab-related AEs that are NCI CTCAE v5.0 Grade <2 or equivalent severity to baseline (except for alopecia; for hypertension and proteinuria, see Section 6.5.1.8)

conditions.name: HIV Positive Eligibility
conditions.description: Conditions for HIV positive participants to be eligible
conditions.text: HIV positive participants excluded unless well controlled on HAART with no AIDS-defining opportunistic infections within last 2 years and CD4 count >350 cells/μL

conditions.name: Hypertension Control Requirement
conditions.description: Hypertension must be controlled before resuming treatment
conditions.text: Hypertension controlled with medication and resolved to Grades 0-2

conditions.name: Grade 3 AE Resolution Criteria
conditions.description: Criteria for resuming treatment after Grade 3 AE
conditions.text: Non-life-threatening and reversible Grade 3 clinical AEs that resolve to Grade ≤1 or pretreatment baseline within 21 to 28 days

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Grade 4 AE
transitionRules.text: If a Grade 4 AE occurs and is deemed at least possibly related to ramucirumab, then ramucirumab should be discontinued except in the specific case of Grade 4 fever or Grade 4 laboratory abnormalities

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Treatment Delay >4 Weeks
transitionRules.text: If a delay of greater than 4 weekly doses is necessary due to ramucirumab-related, unresolved toxicity, ramucirumab SC should be discontinued

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Hypersensitivity Grade 3-4
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for Grade 3-4 hypersensitivity reaction

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Uncontrolled Hypertension
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for uncontrolled hypertension, hypertensive crisis, or hypertensive encephalopathy (Grade 4)

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Arterial/Venous Thromboembolic Events
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for Grade 3 or 4 arterial or venous thromboembolic events

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Bleeding/Hemorrhage Grade 3-4
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for Grade 3 or 4 bleeding/hemorrhage

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for GI Perforation
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for gastrointestinal perforation

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for PRES
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for posterior reversible encephalopathy syndrome

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for CHF Grade 3-4
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for Grade 3 or 4 congestive heart failure

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Fistula Formation
transitionRules.text: Immediately and permanently discontinue ramucirumab for fistula formation

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Nephrotic Syndrome
transitionRules.text: Discontinue study treatment for proteinuria UPCR >3 (or >300 mg/mmol) or in the setting of nephrotic syndrome

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Persistent Proteinuria
transitionRules.text: If UPCR remains ≥2 (or ≥200 mg/mmol) after 14 days, discontinue study treatment

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Second Proteinuria Occurrence
transitionRules.text: Second occurrence of UPCR ≥2: Discontinue study treatment

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Hepatic Encephalopathy
transitionRules.text: Ramucirumab should be discontinued in the event of any new occurrence of hepatic encephalopathy and/or hepatorenal syndrome resulting from liver cirrhosis

transitionRules.name: Dose Modification for Grade 3 AE
transitionRules.text: Dose modifications are permitted only for ramucirumab maintenance dose in the setting of non-life-threatening and reversible Grade 3 clinical AEs considered to be at least possibly related to ramucirumab that resolve to Grade ≤1 or pretreatment baseline within 21 to 28 days

transitionRules.name: Dose Modification for Proteinuria
transitionRules.text: If UPCR ≥2 (or ≥200 mg/mmol), omit ramucirumab dose until UPCR returns to <2. Resume ramucirumab at reduced dose

transitionRules.name: Continuation to Monotherapy
transitionRules.text: If participants have discontinued combination anti-cancer therapy, ramucirumab SC may be continued as monotherapy until progressive disease, at the discretion of the investigator

transitionRules.name: Loading Dose Re-administration
transitionRules.text: Re-administration of loading dose is required only if ≥30 days has elapsed since the last ramucirumab SC dose

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Progressive Disease
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Ramucirumab SC may be continued as monotherapy until progressive disease

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Life-Threatening Event
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Ramucirumab will be permanently discontinued in case of any ramucirumab-related event that is deemed life-threatening, regardless of grade

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Symptomatic Deterioration
scheduleTimelineExits.description: Any symptomatic deterioration or clinical disease progression requiring other forms of specific antitumor systemic therapy will be cause for discontinuation of study therapy

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Wound Healing Complications
scheduleTimelineExits.description: If a participant develops wound-healing complications during therapy, discontinue ramucirumab until the wound is fully healed

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Cycle 1 Weekly Dosing Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for administering each weekly dose in Cycle 1 based on hepatic function criteria

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: New Cycle Start Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for starting each new cycle based on hepatic, hematologic, and AE resolution criteria

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Proteinuria Assessment Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for dose modification based on proteinuria UPCR levels

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Hypertension Management Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for resuming treatment after Grade 3 hypertension

scheduledDecisionInstances.name: Treatment Delay Decision
scheduledDecisionInstances.description: Decision point for continuing or discontinuing treatment based on duration of delay
